Fresh Pi session: EVALUATE PR COMMENTS (single pass, before the loop).

Inputs:
- PR number: {{inputs.pr-number}}
- PR metadata: {{run.dir}}/pr/fetched-pr.json
- Fetched feedback (issue comments, reviews, review comments, status checks): {{run.dir}}/pr/feedback/feedback.json
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

Goal:
Read every comment/review on the PR and turn them into a concrete, bounded list of changes that should be made to address the review feedback. This is a SINGLE evaluation pass BEFORE the make-the-changes loop; do not implement changes here.

Rules:
- Inspect the repository as needed to scope each change.
- Do not edit source code in this step.
- Do not push, create pull requests, or call external product APIs beyond reading repository state.
- Group related comments into discrete change items; for each item give: which comment(s) it answers, the file(s)/area affected, the required change, and an acceptance cue a later reviewer can check.
- If the feedback is empty or requires no action, record that explicitly (status "no_actions").
- Choose a short, safe branch name for the fix work (lowercase letters, numbers, slashes, hyphens; semantic prefix such as feature/ fix/ docs/ refactor/ test/ chore/; never use agent/). Base it on the PR number, e.g. `feature/pr-{{inputs.pr-number}}-fixes`.
- Write the initial manual-testing spec. It must cover: surfaces to test, expected evidence, setup requirements, stale-server hazards, responsive/console checks, acceptance criteria, and provenance expectations for the worktree-rooted test server. Say whether manual testing is required or may be skipped (with an explicit skip rationale/gate if skipped).

Write:
- Changes needed (machine-readable): {{run.dir}}/changes-needed/changes.json
- Summary (human-readable): {{run.dir}}/changes-needed/summary.md
- Branch name: {{run.dir}}/design/branch-name.txt
- Manual-testing spec: {{run.dir}}/manual-testing/spec.md
- Status JSON: {{run.dir}}/changes-needed/status.json

Status JSON examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"N change items produced","issues_file":null}
{"status":"no_actions","summary":"no actionable comments","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"could not evaluate feedback","issues_file":null}

If the feedback is malformed or unreadable, write a failing status with a clear summary.